Vilma Bánky https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vilma_B%C3%A1nky 0 Vilma Bánky (born Vilma Koncsics, 9 January 1901 – 18 March 1991) was a Hungarian-born American silent film actress, although the early part of her acting career began in Budapest, spreading to France, Austria, and Germany. Bánky was best known for her roles in The Eagle and The Son of the Sheik with Rudolph Valentino and several romantic teamings with Ronald Colman.
